SIMPLE: tiff
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tiff
<hw>Tiff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Originally, a sniff,
sniffing; cf. Icel. <ets><?/efr</ets> a smell, <ets><?/efa</ets> to
sniff, Norw. <ets>tev</ets> a drawing in of the breath, <ets>teva</ets>
to sniff, smell, dial. Sw. <ets>t⟦uum⟧v</ets> smell, scent,
taste.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Liquor; especially, a small draught of
liquor.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sipping his <xex>tiff</xex> of brandy punch.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fit of anger or peevishness; a slight altercation
or contention. See <er>Tift</er>.</def> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiff</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tiff
<hw>Tiff</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Tiffed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tiffing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To be in a pet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She <qex>tiffed</qex> with Tim, she ran from Ralph.</q>
<rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiff</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tiff
<hw>Tiff</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>tiffen</ets>, OF.
<ets>tiffer</ets>, <ets>tifer</ets>, to bedizen; cf. D.
<ets>tippen</ets> to clip the points or ends of the hair, E.
<ets>tip</ets>, n.]</ety> <def>To deck out; to dress.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>A. Tucker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiffany</ent>⟦br⟧
